-- Westport Fuel-Oil Teams in Singapore, Nashville Said to Join LDH
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2012-05-16T06:54:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/westport-fuel-oil-teams-in-singapore-nashville-said-to-join-ldh.html
Seven people from Westport Petroleum
Inc.’s fuel-oil trading team in Singapore and Nashville,
Tennessee, are leaving for Louis Dreyfus Highbridge Energy LLC,
according to two people with knowledge of the situation.  Three people are departing Westport’s Singapore office and
will stay in the city with LDH Energy, according to the people.
The remaining four, who were based in Nashville, will work for
LDH in Houston, they said.  Pasadena , California-based Westport
is a wholly owned subsidiary of  Mitsui & Co. (8031)  Reuters reported
the departures on May 4.  Alex Plantilla, an official at Westport in Pasadena, didn’t
return a phone message left at his office. An official at
Stanford, Connecticut-based LDH Energy declined to comment when
contacted by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Kwiatkowski in Singapore at 
